Articles.Content:
I have installed Kerbal Engineer Redux.

I can apparently save subassemblies into the folder C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Kerbal Space Program\saves\MERCURY\Subassemblies but I cannot load them. Screenshot shows the problem:

![EOHJO64.jpg](http://i.imgur.com/EOHJO64.jpg)

Could you please post a list of other installed mods as well as the particular subassembally files that youre using, this will help me to reproduce the issue.

Thanks

--Nitebomber

EDIT: After some time playing with the subassemblies for a while, The only method Ive found of not being able to load a subassembly is if the craft file is in some way broken, such as syntax being incorrect or the craft file referancing a part that isnt present, Ive not been able to find a way of saving something to the subassembly and not being able to retrieve it, but I shall keep looking. As for adding something to the subassembly file structure and it not appearing, Try just reloading the VAB instance, It looks to me like youve saved it and not had the VAB instance reload the subassembly "Crafts". I await your reply.

**Edited <time datetime="2015-07-12T11:05:25Z" title="07/12/2015 11:05  AM" data-short="8 yr">July 12, 2015</time> by nitebomber51**

the PODX craft file is somehow corrupted. KSP will test craft files when you go to use them and the program will not load a craft file that it doesn't think is valid. KSP will not even show it in the GUI. Not much you can do about it, I would recommend recreating that subassembly from scratch. If you name it the same you will get prompted to overwrite.
